Text: This week I mostly spent time rewriting the JavaScript to accommodate the new API route that Roro put in that allows us to retrieve all suppliers in a 200 mile radius that supply all materials.
I then process this information in JavaScript to allow the information to be updated more quickly as long as the search location doesn't change. As shown below.
While it may be unnecessary feature that does slow down load times a little I think it's kind of neat.
We had another meeting with Eric to show the current prototype.
He seemed pleased with the results but still wanted to add and change a lot of features.
Mainly that he wants us to change to a satellite view so that you can confirm a suppliers location based on if you see a hole in the ground or not.
We may have an attempt at converting this to Google Maps to have that option if we end up having the time but it doesn't seem likely.
As for things that I can improve on - this week I haven't done as much work as I probably should have, I think I was just starting to feel a little overwhelmed and needed a moment to catch my breath.
When it comes to working with Kuku we haven't collaborated very well, I'm sure this is a fault on both parties.
I should have been trying to include him more with the current work but he also should have been more proactive in getting involved.

I'm not entirely sure but maybe it's the fact I'm not used to working with people on the same piece of code and somewhere deep down I don't trust others with code I've written, it's something I'll need to think a bit more on.

But anyway as a step in the right direction I've scheduled a collaborative in person work session with Kuku on Monday where we'll hopefully get a fair bit of work done and come up with a plan on what we think we can get done by the end of the project.
